description: Do nothing unless the user explicitly says to do it
alwaysApply: true
---

# Do Nothing Unless User Says So

- **No actions** unless the user clearly instructs an action (e.g. "do this", "run this", "create X", "change Y").
- **No edits, no commands, no file creation** in response to a question or a vague wish.
- **Questions and "I want..." without "do it" / "make it" / "run it"** = answer or clarify only. Do not execute.
- If in doubt, do nothing. Ask instead: "Do you want me to do that?"
